Explanation:

The documents mention that the film Hairspray (2007) deals with issues of racial segregation and fat-shaming, but most notably it mentions the romantic relationship between Tracy and Link as being based on personality rather than physical attractiveness. However, they also highlight the issue of interracial romance in general through the subplot involving Penny and her black boyfriend. Additionally, one of the documents mentions that Hairspray's portrayal of history may lack depth to the time it is set, but it does depict the backdrop of a white musical love story amidst the Civil Rights Movement.

The correct interpretation would be that while Hairspray (2007) primarily focuses on the theme of Tracy's self-love journey and being an intersectional masterpiece with regards to its portrayal of non-conventionally attractive female characters in relationships, it does touch upon and highlight the theme of interracial romance through the subplot involving Penny.
